üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. GDPR primarily focuses on the protection of:
A. Network infrastructure
B. Personal data of individuals
C. Financial transactions
D. Intellectual property

2. GDPR applies to organizations that:
A. Are located only in Europe
B. Process EU residents‚Äô personal data
C. Use ISO standards
D. Perform audits

3. Which of the following is considered personal data under GDPR?
A. Server IP only
B. Email address of an individual
C. Company registration number
D. Firewall configuration

4. Sensitive personal data under GDPR includes:
A. Username
B. Health and biometric data
C. Office address
D. Job title

5. GDPR is best described as a:
A. Voluntary framework
B. Mandatory regulation
C. Security tool
D. Audit guideline

6. ISO/IEC 2700x series mainly deals with:
A. Network protocols
B. Information security management
C. Software development
D. Incident hacking

7. ISO/IEC 27001 focuses on establishing a:
A. Firewall architecture
B. ISMS (Information Security Management System)
C. SOC
D. Penetration testing lab

8. ISO standards are generally:
A. Mandatory laws
B. Voluntary standards
C. Country-specific laws
D. Penalties

9. ISO/IEC 27001 certification helps organizations to:
A. Eliminate cyber attacks
B. Demonstrate security best practices
C. Avoid audits
D. Reduce documentation

10. GDPR compliance failure may result in:
A. Only technical issues
B. Heavy fines and legal penalties
C. Improved security
D. No impact

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. Which GDPR principle ensures data is collected for a specific purpose?
A. Accuracy
B. Purpose limitation
C. Integrity
D. Storage limitation

12. ‚ÄúLawfulness, fairness, and transparency‚Äù is a:
A. GDPR penalty
B. GDPR core principle
C. Audit phase
